8ï¸âƒ£ Common Interview Follow-ups (Be Ready)
	â“ What is cache invalidation?

	Removing or expiring outdated cache data when underlying data changes.

	â“ Why avoid caching ActiveRecord objects?

	Schema changes or code changes can break deserialization and cause stale data.


â“ Redis vs Memcached?

	| Redis                    | Memcached        |
	| ------------------------ | ---------------- |
	| Persistent               | In-memory only   |
	| Supports data structures | Simple key-value |
	| Slower but flexible      | Faster           |


â­ 30-Second Perfect Answer (MEMORIZE THIS)

â€œRails handles caching using multiple strategies like fragment caching, low-level data caching, and HTTP caching.
It supports different cache stores such as MemoryStore, Memcached, and Redis, with Redis commonly used in production.
Rails uses cache keys with timestamps to automatically expire cache when records change.
This helps reduce database queries and improves response time.â€